gurmukhi: ਕਿਤੇਕ ਭਾਜ ਚਾਲੀਯੰ ਸੁਰੇਸ ਲੋਗ ਕੋ ਗੲੇ ॥ ਨਿਸੰਤ ਜੀਤ ਜੀਤ ਕੈ ਅਨੰਤ ਸੂਰਮਾ ਲੲੇ ॥੧੯॥
transliteration: Kitek Bhaaj Dhaaleeyan Sures Log Ko Gad|| Nisant Jeet Jeet Kai Anant Soormaa Lae||19||
translation: Many people came running under the refuge of gods, and Suraj, who ends the night, conquered many warriors.19.

gurmukhi: ਸਮੱਟ ਸੇਲ ਸਾਮੁਹੇ ਸਰੱਕ ਸੂਰ ਝਾੜਹੀਂ ॥ ਬਬੱਕ ਬਾਘ ਜਯੋਂ ਬਲੀ ਹਲੱਕ ਹਾਕ ਮਾਰਹੀਂ ॥
transliteration: Samatt Sel Saamuhe Sarakk Soor Jhaad-heen|| Babakk Baagh Jyon Balihalakk Haak Maar-heen||
translation: The warriors are striking the daggers, holding them tightly and coming face to face and the brave fighters are challenging one another, roaring like the lions.

gurmukhi: ਅਭੰਗ ਅੰਗ ਭੰਗ ਹ੍ਵੈ ੳੁਤੰਗ ਜੰਗ ਮੋ ਗਿਰੇ ॥ ਸੁਰੰਗ ਸੂਰਮਾ ਸਭੈ ਨਿਸੰਗ ਜਾਨ ਕੈ ਅਰੇ ॥੨੦॥
transliteration: Abhan An Bhan Hvai Outan Jan Mo Gire|| Suran Soormaa Sabhai Nisan Jaan Kaidare||20||
translation: The firm limbs, after swinging continuously, are falling down and the brave and beautiful fighters, fearlessly coming face to face with others are clashing.20.

gurmukhi: ਨਵੰ ਨਿਸਾਣ ਬਾਜੀਯੰ ॥ ਘਟਾ ਘਮੰਡ ਲਾਜੀਯੰ ॥
transliteration: Navan Nisaan Baajeeyan|| Ghataa Ghamannd Laajeeyan||
translation: Listening to the resonance of the trumpets, the clouds are feeling shy.

gurmukhi: ਤਬੱਲ ਤੁੰਦਰੰ ਬਜੇ ॥ ਸੁਣੰਤ ਸੂਰਮਾ ਗਜੇ ॥੨੧॥
transliteration: Taball Toundran Baje|| Sounant Soormaa Gade||21||
translation: The fastened trumpets have resounded and haring their sound, the warriors are thundering.21.

gurmukhi: ਸੁ ਜੂਝਿ ਜੂਝਿ ਕੈ ਪਰੈਂ ॥ ਸੁਰੇਸ ਲੋਗ ਬਿਚਰੈਂ ॥
transliteration: Su Joojh(i) Kai Darain|| Sures Log Bichrain||
translation: Fighting ferociously, the gods and their kings are moving (here and there).

gurmukhi: ਚੜੈ ਬਿਵਾਨ ਸੋਭਹੀ ॥ ਅਦੇਵ ਦੇਵ ਲੋਭਹੀ ॥੨੨॥
transliteration: Chadai Bivaan Sobh-hee|| Adev Dev Lobh-hee||22||
translation: They are roaming by mountain on air-vehicles and the harts of the gods and demons both are feeling envious.22.

gurmukhi: ਡਹ ਡਹ ਸੁ ਡਾਮਰ ਡੰਕਣੀ ॥ ਕਹ ਕਹ ਸੁ ਕੂਕਤ ਜੋਗਣੀ ॥
transliteration: Dah Dah Su Daankanee|| Kah Kah Su Kookat Jogadee||
translation: The sound of he tabors of vampires and the cries of the Yoginis are being heard.

gurmukhi: ਝਮ ਝਮਕ ਸਾਂਗ ਝਮੱਕੀਯੰ ॥ ਰਣ ਗਾਜ ਬਾਜ ੳੁਥੱਕੀਯੰ ॥੨੩॥
transliteration: Jham Jhamak Saan Jhamakkeeyan|| Ran Gadj Baaj Outhakkeeyan||23||
translation: The daggers are glistening and glittering and the elephants and horses are jumping in the battlefield.23.

gurmukhi: ਢਮ ਢਮਕ ਢੋਲ ਢਮੱਕੀਯੰ ॥ ਝਲ ਝਲਕ ਤੇਗ ਝਲੱਕੀਯੰ ॥
transliteration: Dham Dhamak Dhol Dhamakkeeyan|| Jhal Jhalak Teg Jhalakkeeyan||
translation: The resonance of drum is being heard and the luster of swords is glimmering.

gurmukhi: ਜਟ ਛੋਰ ਰੁਦ੍ਰ ਤਹ ਨੱਚੀਯੰ ॥ ਬਿਕ੍ਰਾਰ ਮਾਰ ਜਹ ਮੱਚੀਯੰ ॥੨੪॥
transliteration: Jat Chhodh Rudra Tah Nachcheeyan|| Bikraar Maar Jah Machcheeyan||24||
translation: Rudra is also dancing there with his loosened matted hair and a dreadful war is being waged there.24.
